The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, June 8: The BSE sensex crashed nearly 438 points  the third-biggest fall of the year  to end at 14665.92 on the back of profit booking by foreign institutional investors and others. The sensex opened on a higher ground at 15153.21 and rose to the days high of 15200.82 before closing at 14665.92, down 437.63 points or 2.90 per cent from its previous close. Extremely weak trends in European markets and US futures also weighed on the local bourses.                            
	 Mumbai, June 8: Pfizer Animal Health has acquired the animal healthcare division of RFCL, Vetnex from ICICI Venture Funds Management for an undisclosed sum. ICICI Venture had bought RFCL from Ranbaxy in 2005. The acquisition is expected to close by August, subject to necessary regulatory approvals.                             
	 New Delhi, June 8: The Supreme Court today allowed Chennai-based two-wheeler company TVS Motor Company to manufacture TVS Flame, a 125-cc bike sporting twin-spark plugs, the technology for which Bajaj Auto allegedly holds the patent rights.                            
	 New Delhi, June 8: The DMK today opposed the Centres disinvestment policy, a few days after President Pratibha Patil talked in favour of listing of state-run firms. The political party had successfully stalled disinvestment plans of the previous UPA regime.                             
	 New Delhi, June 8: The finance ministry has imposed a provisional anti-dumping duty ranged between $17.52 and $63.84 per 1,000 pieces on compact discs-recordable (CDR) imported from countries such as Iran, Thailand and Korea.                                                                                                                           
